properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 23 at 10:29PM AKST until January 25 at 3:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. The cold wind chills
will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to exposed
skin. Expect wind chills as cold as 45 below zero.

* WHERE...Denali south of the Park Entrance.

* WHEN...6 PM this evening to 3 PM Saturday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...North winds gusting to 30 mph will cause
areas of blowing and drifting snow. Cold wind chills as low as
45 below zero will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin. Travelers should be prepared for snow drifts and
very cold wind chills.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Advisory means that cold air and sustained wind
speeds of 15 mph or more will create low wind chills. Frost bite
and hypothermia can occur if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 3 PM AKST SATURDAY
